Backstage at the Olympia, the Gymshark team surprised me with this shirt—whether they knew I was retiring or not, it was a powerful reminder of the confidence those around me have always had in me, even before the win was certain.

For the first time this year, I felt the confidence in myself that others have had in me. A decade of hard work and growth has brought me to a place where I can truly believe in what I’ve built. Grateful, humbled, and ready for what’s next.

The Gymshark Diffuse Sweat Headband is coming back 💪

45% of Black women admit to avoiding exercise to keep their hairstyles intact. We want to help.

We’re re-launching our headband in both single and double-layer options in Black, Base Green and Fetch Pink. 

Designed with the Black community and all hair types in mind, our headband supports you through all your training. So you’ve got one less thing to think about and only your workout to focus on.

Dropping in selected regions on October 23rd. Coming to the US very soon 👀

Gymshark x @steelwarriors.

We’re partnering with Steel Warriors, an anti-knife crime charity who are on a mission to take knives off the street, melt them down and turn the steel into outdoor gyms.

Our shared goal is to transform young people’s lives by giving them more access to fitness and helping to reduce the endemic of knife crime in the UK.

@gymshark x BELCAST signature series!!

Padrinos estoy muy emocionado de compartir este gran momento con ustedes. Esta colección representa mi vibra, mi estilo, mi historia y mis sueños desde México para el mundo. Más que un simple producto, esta colaboración es un logro personal en mi vida que estoy muy emocionado de compartir con todos.

Esto no sucedió de la noche a la mañana. Detrás de la serie, ha habido sacrificio, noches de insomnio, desafíos, entrenamiento intenso, trabajo duro y el estilo de vida que tanto me esfuerzo por lograr. Espero que sientan eso con estos productos y creo que con un trabajo duro y genuino, los sueños pueden hacerse realidad.
Estoy emocionado de presentar mi serie Gymshark Signature. Espero que te guste tanto como a mí.

Si estás en este LIFT NY puedes conseguir mis signature series exclusivamente aquí y en 2 semanas pueden conseguirlo en el dropset de Gymshark padrinos!!

My next chapter with Gymshark…. CREATIVE DIRECTOR 🗒️💬📱🫧💭

I’m beyond honored and excited to announce… I’m stepping into a new role at Gymshark. The Creative Director of future Adapt Collections ‼️❤️‍🔥

I found such a deep love and passion while working with the brilliant design and creative teams to bring 5 of my very own collections with Gymshark to life.

As I step into this new role, I now have the insane opportunity as Creative Director to be able to design, influence and guide the new Adapt collections. Collections that have always been my very favorite and given me the confidence to feel my best in and outside of the gym.

I can’t wait to show y’all what we’ve got in the works... 👀 Keep your eyes on our socials 🫶 #Gymshark

6 years ago, I decided enough was enough. I was tired of being the smallest kid in my year. I would stay up late at night secretly doing push ups and sit-ups on my bedroom floor once everyone had gone to sleep. Shortly after, I gained confidence and decided to go to my school gym where the instructor taught me about weight training, starting off with weighted Calisthenics moves to follow suit with my gymnastics background. 

I remember buying my first Gymshark pieces and wearing them to that gym, it felt like I was putting on a superhero uniform. From then on I’ve felt unstoppable. And every single day, I have something to be proud of.

i started my fitness journey to regain my power, both mentally and physically. in the past, people have taken away my power and made me feel like my body wasn’t mine anymore. i ended up resenting my body and never felt happy in my own skin. this led me to lose myself completely and i had never felt more powerless. 

it wasn’t until i began my physical and mental health journey, where i was able to slowly find myself again and regain the power that i had felt was once taken from me. i’ve learned to be proud of my body and to never take it for granted again. as a woman, there is nothing more empowering than becoming both physically and mentally strong in a world that views us as weak. fitness is so much more than just lifting heavy weights, it’s a journey… and it can truly change your life if you let it. 

whenever i wear gymshark, i feel powerful. it’s so much more than just activewear, it’s a community. the world wide @gymshark black friday sale is still live with deals up to 70% off!💜

Vive tu cultura means to live your culture. 

Being hispanic means, unity, family, culture, sacrifice, and love. Hispanic Heritage Month is coming to an end, but we will continue to live our culture EVERYDAY. To mark this year’s celebration, we brought the lifting and Hispanic community together to transform and create a space where we are welcomed. It’s deeper than just lifting, this is what brings us together, what forms a unity. It’s a remarkable and beautiful thing to have witnessed in our community. Even though it was dedicated to Hispanic Heritage Month, I hope that it creates a movement to impact every different culture/ethnicity. I’m forever grateful and I will appreciate this moment forever, thank you a lot. 🤍 @gymshark

I’m so excited to announce the Leana x Gymshark graphic collection. Drops Thursday, August 31st at 9am MST/4pm GMT

This graphic collection is the first start to making change. Designed by me in summer 23, a time where I truly resonated and understood the meaning of “discomfort is where growth occurs” . This past summer I made some of the biggest decisions of my life reconnecting with my faith.  During this time I learned how to enjoy the feeling of discomfort knowing that growth will occur, and it has. It’s also led me to become more creative, understand fashion, quality, and how to express my feelings through clothing. This is just the beginning of what’s to come…. Mark your calendars,this will be limited edition🤍

Meet the girls of @saltleywfc, a Birmingham-based women's football team inspiring young women of all abilities and backgrounds to participate in outdoor sports 🙌

Saltley Stallions Women's FC, CO-founded by @obayedhussain and @yas.nessa, is a community encouraging women to get involved in recreational football sessions. Set up in 2019 with just 4 players, the team now has over 200 women and girls who take part in open access football sessions and regular five a side leagues. They've since renovated a shipping container into an on-site gym to support the team's training.

With South Asian participation in sports often being overlooked, it is @obayedhussain and @yas.nessa’s goal to ensure Saltley Stallions Women's FC is a community available for everyone of all abilities to inspire many generations to come.

Strength of faith meets strength of body.

We asked Muslim members of the Gymshark family to share stories of what Ramadan means to them, their communities and their fitness journeys. Here's how @realrubaali commits to their faith and training throughout this month...

Ramadan to me is a month of purification, heightened devotion and self-reflection. It’s truly a cleanse for the mind, body and soul.

Some might see Ramadan as a “setback” for their fitness goals - but I see it otherwise. I see it as a challenge to push my body and mind to go beyond its own limits.

It’s remarkable how much the body is capable of when the mind is the commander. Over the years, I’ve trained my mind to understand that it’s all mental. I don’t take shortcuts just because I’m fasting. Whether my body is fed or not, I show up every day with effort and determination to be better. It’s all about adapting to your circumstances and finding what works best for you.

During Ramadan I gain far more willpower than any other month of the year. For my brothers and sisters who are preparing for Ramadan, remember that with sacrifice comes success. With hardship comes ease. And with determination you can gain the benefits of Ramadan while improving your fitness. Stay strong, always.

I started bodybuilding because I was very skinny and insecure. I wanted to look and feel more masculine about myself. I am a transgender man, but I never allowed that to define who I was or my capabilities.

After following a strict training and dieting regime I put on a large amount of muscle mass in a considerably short amount of time, where then I decided to compete in my first bodybuilding show.

#BlackLivesMatter

We want you guys to meet Alex, a member of  the Gymshark community, who has been attending peaceful protests but also helping to clean up the streets of New York after some turned violent.
-
“The experience of my first protest in NYC, I did not know what I was getting myself into, but I was aware of the risks that I was taking. I had a lot of people tell me, don’t go, because it’s dangerous. I still went because seeing is believing. There was nothing dangerous about the protest, but knowledge.
But I will say that if you do protest, leave early. There is nothing good during the night. All parents should educate their children a little more about what’s going on currently. After all of the chaos was done the next day, I felt bad for what the youth did in my neighborhood, and I don’t blame them for being misguided. I woke up at 6am and left my house to make it to the location where they destroyed by 8am to clean up my neighborhood. Was I mad at them? No, because I understand that’s how they expressed themselves and others did take advantage of a sensitive situation. My advice for viewers would be to not listen to what others and social media have to say. Nothing is better than an in-person experience.”
📸 + 📝: @alexwgoals 
#BlackLivesMatter

Strength has no identity, only unity. We’re working closely with our team, our athletes, and our entire community to unite against injustice and make a genuine difference, not just a statement.

In our world of sports, strength and conditioning, we’re used to seeing black athletes as icons, heroes and teammates. We should not be used to seeing injustice against black friends, family and strangers.

We thank our friends in the industry - from @Nike to @Adidas to @Lululemon - for their outspoken commitment to the cause. Because silence is not impartiality. It’s ignorance. And tomorrow is not soon enough. We must push for change today.
